First, switch to xfce4:
  sudo update-alternatives --config x-session-manager
  -> /usr/bin/xfce4-session

https://wiki.haskell.org/Xmonad/Using_xmonad_in_XFCE 
  - at bottom: Debian Wheezy
    settings manager: run xfce4-settings-manager
  - same xmonad.hs from manjaro

disable xfdesktop:
  session and startup -> current session -> xfdesktop ->
    change restart style: immediately -> never
  https://feeblenerd.blogspot.com/2015/11/pretty-i3-with-xfce.html?m=1

whisker menu:
  https://www.debugpoint.com/xfce-whisker-menu/

screensaver settings: disable screensaver and lock screen
